What makes a great trainer?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Arguably, one of the most important and most prominent characteristics of a good trainer is the ability to communicate effectively. Often, an organisation decides to offer training on a very challenging topic or sensitive material. For this reason, a trainer must be able to clearly and concisely teach the content.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is a trainer job description?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>A corporate trainer is a specialist responsible for increasing a company's productivity by teaching new skills and knowledge to employees. They use seminars, lectures, and team exercises to update employees on company goals and procedures. They also refer to as a technical trainer.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is skill training?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The design skills training is to provide employees with the targeted practice they need to gain the knowledge and abilities necessary to fulfil the specific requirements of their job positions. Skills training can also use to re-educate and retrain employees whenever new technology, processes or systems debut.</p>
</div>
